ccording to the <a href=\"http://triblive.com/news/fayette/8936263-74/film-bill-buffalo#axzz3jFKQu75K\">Pittsburgh Tribune Review</a>, the house was purchased by a couple in the 1970s who were approached in 1989 to ask if their house could be used in the hit film. The film-makers shot the exterior as well as the foyer and dining room.</p> <p>“They were looking for a home in which you entered the front door and had a straight line through,” home-owner Barbara Lloyd said. “They wanted it to look like a spider web, with Buffalo Bill drawing Jodie Foster into the foyer, into the kitchen, then into the basement.”<br /></p>  <figure class=\"element element-tweet\" data-canonical-url=\"https://twitter.com/TribLIVE/statuses/633986295547699201\">  <blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Have a friend for dinner at this Fayette house from &quot;Silence of the Lambs,&quot; now for sale. <a href=\"http://t.co/NimBuS1Wri\">http://t.co/NimBuS1Wri</a> <a href=\"http://t.co/41ZxCYcD0x\">pic.twitter.com/41ZxCYcD0x</a></p>&mdash; TribLIVE.com (@TribLIVE) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/TribLIVE/status/633986295547699201\">August 19, 2015</a></blockquote>  </figure>  <p>Diane Wilk is the estate agent looking after the property and she believes its notoriety could be a major selling point.</p> <p>“People love to be scared,” she said. “I could see somebody doing something fun with this.”</p>","productionOffice":"UK","hasStoryPackage":"false","trailText":"The fictional killer’s house from the 1991 hit is available in Pittsburgh for $300,000. Dungeon not included<br>","headline":"Killer deal: Buffalo Bill's home from Silence of the Lambs up for sale","byline":"Benjamin Lee","commentable":"true"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/aug/19/buffalo-bill-home-silence-of-the-lambs-sale","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/aug/19/buffalo-bill-home-silence-of-the-lambs-sale","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/thriller","webTitle":"Thriller","